name: Seattle Donut Boat Rentals
description: Seattle Donut Boat is Lake Union’s most unique boat rental experience in the heart of Seattle. Get out on the water and go where you want to go. It's easy to drive, no experience needed. See stunning city views, iconic houseboats, seaplanes, Gasworks Park, and more. Bring food and drinks and experience your own private picnic on the West Coast's most active lake.

name: Chef Guided Chocolate & Coffee Tour
description:
This downtown chef guided walking tour takes your palate on a discovery of the most delicious chocolate and coffee in Seattle. Visit a bean-to-bar factory, savor ganache confections made with real ingredients and learn about the iconic Fran's salted caramel. Explore the coffee scene both new and learn about roasters who have shaped the industry. Get tips and tricks from your chef guide on how to improve your cup of joe in the morning or make your own sweets at home.

All highlighted companies are local Seattle businesses with a story that stems from a passion to source soundly and make decadent sweets or beverages. This is a unique way to explore Seattle, its small businesses and savor our local delicacies.

We keep groups small- 10 people or less!

Only chef guided tour available

itemListElement.name: Whidbey Island Deception Pass Private SUV Tour

name: Whidbey Island Deception Pass Private SUV Tour
description:
Private tour for 2-5 people in our comfortable and clean SUV. Deception Pass Bridge has fantastic views of the saltwater inlet to Puget Sound. Walking across this 180 foot high bridge over Puget Sound and ocean waters is an exciting experience. The rocks on the beach are fascinating, so many colors!

Your choice of restaurants in quaint Coupeville
Sound views
Historic Fort Casey
Ferry ride

review.name: Whidbey Island experience
review.reviewBody: We did a private tour of Whidbey Island and came away very impressed with the knowledge of Cheryl, our guide, as well as her level of customer service. We visited state parks with breathtaking views, Fort Casey and its historical sites, and several quaint little towns that we totally enjoyed walking around. She was quite flexible and tailored the tour to our timeframe and interests. We strongly recommend her.

review.name: Great way to experience greater Seattle area that's not just about downtown!
review.reviewBody: First time in Seattle, and we like to know local flavors and get a "lay of the land". Really easy to book and communicate with Cheryl. Scott was fantastic, affable, knowledgeable and totally flexible with what we wanted to experience from the tour. He gave a lot of insider tips and insight to the history, character of Whidbey and surrounding area. Was really cool to learn about the natural landscape as well. Definitely experience the mussels in Coupville! Never had fresh caught, straight from the water to the plate mussels before. Happy that we got to experience an aspect of the greater Seattle area that's not just about downtown!

name: Conversation
description: Conversation Kitchen & Bar is Thompson Seattle’s signature new American restaurant that offers an approachable fine dining experience in a welcoming setting curated to foster conversation and ignite a sense of community. Our menus offer an array of thoughtfully prepared dishes, focused on fresh local produce, farm-raised proteins, and the best ingredients the Pacific Northwest has to offer.

itemListElement.name: San Juan Island Day Trip from Seattle

name: San Juan Island Day Trip from Seattle
description: Cruise out of downtown Seattle’s Pier 69 in the morning and soak in breathtaking scenery on your journey from Seattle to Friday Harbor. Catch sight of the stately Cascade Range as you clip past the eastern coast of Whidbey Island and glide under the impressive and historic Deception Pass. Upon your arrival in Friday Harbor, wander the town’s picturesque streets, stop by Lime Kiln State Park, rent a bike or grab a bite to eat in one of the many restaurants. Return to Seattle that evening on the 5:15 PM sailing.

review.name: Beautiful trip!
review.reviewBody: Enjoy a full day of cruising and relaxation!  Deception Pass was a highlight of the trip for us.  Walking around the quaint little town was fun and then we had lunch on the water.  A very nice day!!

review.name: Friday Harbour and Whale Watching On Seattle Clipper
review.reviewBody: This is a long 12 hour return day trip with most of the time spent on the boat if you take the Whale Watching option. We enjoyed spectacular views of the Puget Sound and saw orcas, seals, sea lions and eagles. Brief stop off in Friday Harbour for a walk round marina and nice lunch in a roof top bar (Fridays Chowder House) - we wouldn’t do the day trip again as it was tiring for us but glad we did it the once, we would probably stay for a few nights on San Juan Island next time and take shorter whale watching trip from Friday Harbour on smaller boat. It was a nice day but cool breeze on deck as boat is fast moving - recommend boarding early for best window seats in cabin. Trip was pretty pricey at $300 for 2 adults but it’s a fast comfortable boat and snacks and drinks in galley are good value.

itemListElement.name: Mount Rainier National Park - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch

name: Mount Rainier National Park - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch
description: Explore pristine alpine meadows, wander through magical old growth forests, and watch roaring glacial waterfalls crash into rugged canyons on this private day tour to Mount Rainier National Park. The snow-capped peak, encased in over 35 square miles (91 km²) of ice year-round, is endearingly referred to locally as “The Mountain” and is a must-visit Seattle day trip. Throughout the day, you'll enjoy meaningful commentary on the history, culture, and geology of the region from an expert local guide. The tour includes a gourmet lunch, park admission, and pick-up/drop-off at your Seattle hotel in our luxury Mercedes van.

review.name: Amazing experience with a great owner/operator tour guide!
review.reviewBody: I highly recommend this tour. Daniel uses every moment to maximize your learning experience. We were able to see amazing falls, a clear view of Mount Rainier and the lunch experience was  hands down one of the best I’ve had in park.  Daniel is super smart, friendly and patient!!

review.name: What a Perfect Day!
review.reviewBody:
We strongly recommend this tour! It was even better than expected and the highlight of our trip to Seattle!

Daniel picked us up (arrived early!) and led us through a delightful day of sightseeing, hiking, and learning. Transport was comfortable and safe and equipped with chargers and refreshments. 

Our tour ran pretty much exactly as described, with the variations being guest-initiated and to our benefit. (One example: a brief stop to get a pic under the National Park sign on our way in turned into a pit-stop to buy cherries, which we were slated to do on the way out of the park.) The tour felt intimate and relaxed from the start!

While broadly knowledgeable about the greater Seattle area and Mt Rainier park, Daniel kept the "instruction" manageable-- not bogged down in facts and detail but specific enough that we have a better understanding of the geography, flora, and fauna of the park. He fielded questions (a LOT of questions) with aplomb and patience and was highly responsive to the group needs. Our family of 4 (parents & two teens) was joined by a second group, a pair of old friends. Daniel chose hikes (walks) that suited the group as a whole and allowed members to move at our own paces. 

While our family may have opted for a little more vigorous a hike, or maybe a longer hike at the Paradise area, the agenda Daniel set really gave us a good overview of the park, the geography of various elevations, and a sense that we'd seen a lot. One highlight was the walk down to the riverbed, which was refreshing (that cold snowmelt water!) and humbling (the sheer scale of it!). That the weather was *perfect* and everyone we met was smiling certainly contributed to the overall sense of joy.

The attention to his guests' experience extended to lunch, which was phenomenal and included a vegetarian & peanut-free meal for our daughter. Served family-style, it was a nice opportunity to sit and get to know one another in a shady picnic spot. I appreciate that Daniel uses all reusable items throughout the trip-- from travel mugs for our coffee to silver wear and cloth napkins at lunch-- reflecting his respect for the land he so obviously loves.

By the end of the trip, we all felt as though we'd not only visited a beautiful and important place, but that we'd connected with some beautiful humans, as well. Daniel set a positive and inclusive tone and was engaging and considerate-- he really made it easy to have a great day!

review.name: Mt Rainier Tour
review.reviewBody: Excellent guide, beautiful scenery, great lunch. Tour guide and owner Daniel was knowledgeable and entertaining.

review.name: The Absolute Best Experience
review.reviewBody:
My husband and I had two wonderful day tours with Daniel in early June this year.  We were most fortunate to be his first tours following being closed for the pandemic, so our small group tour was in fact a private tour.  The food was wonderful from morning coffee and pastries to a delectable lunch with lovely Washington wines.  The van was most comfortable and the well planned rest stops were greatly appreciated.  

The scenery was incredible and the insider’s knowledge that Daniel provided added a truly special touch.

review.name: The best part of our Seattle Vacation
review.reviewBody: My family and I had the most amazing tour of Mr. Rainier. I absolutely recommend Yonder Sky if you plan on doing tours in Washington. Our driver, Daniel, who is also the small business owner, was raised in the Seattle area so questions/answers started as soon as we hopped in the car. There were 7 of us in the brand new Mercedes van. I would've thought it would be cramped, but it was not. It was very comfortable. The 7 of us were a part of 3 groups so we all got to know one another and before you know it we were at a rest stop for pastries - and these were not national store bought, but from a local bakery and they were delicious. We had juices, sodas, waters, and more to choose from. Then we headed to the mountain. We made several stops that provided different breath taking views and Daniel was respectful of allowing us the time to stay and take it in. He also did not rush us back to the car. (some of those hikes take different hikers more or less time) I can't choose just one highlight of the trip because there were so many for all different reasons, but our lunch put this trip over the top. The place was busy, but Daniel drove right up to a private picnic table where we were by ourselves with only views of trees and sky. The meal which was comprised of about 5-6 different fresh, homemade creations. We enjoyed wine, soda, water, and juice and we basically feasted with a great group of folks. Due to time, Daniel was able to go above and beyond and take us to an additional view which was so worth it. He handed us out delicious cookies. I have to remark that he is so good with people, he was even able to get interact in an engaging way with my 11 and 10 year olds. Before we knew it we had been away from the city most of the day and it was time to head home. I think the majority of us closed our eyes briefly which was really nice. Each group raved about our experience to Daniel. I am really glad we went with Yonder Sky tours. I saw bigger groups but each view was more crowded for them, each walk seemed longer and slower. We were able to maneuver in a way catered just to our small group so well worth it. Daniel is a very nice young man and if we ever go back, we will do the island tour or a winery tour with him!

review.name: Fantastic way to see more of Mt Rainier
review.reviewBody: Daniel provided an amazing tour of Mt Rainier for our small group.  Although several of us had been to Mt Rainier years ago, Daniel took us to some spectacular waterfalls and other stops we didn’t know existed in the National Park.  Daniel’s enthusiasm and the knowledge he shared with us about the park, as well as his incredible hospitality made the day a memorable one.  Not to mention, lunch was delicious!  I highly recommend this tour, whether for visitors to the area or long-time local residents, you’re sure to enjoy your day and learn something new.

itemListElement.name: Olympic National Park - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch

name: Olympic National Park - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch
description: Witness stunning mountain vistas, pristine alpine meadows, and dense old growth forests on this private day tour to Olympic National Park. We'll start the day with a beautiful ferry ride from Seattle followed by a scenic drive to this UNESCO World Heritage Site, where we'll explore one of the best-preserved natural landscapes in the world. Throughout the day, you'll enjoy meaningful commentary on the history, culture, and geology of the region from an expert local guide. The tour includes a gourmet lunch, park admission, and pick-up/drop-off at your Seattle hotel in our luxury Mercedes van.

review.name: An Extremely Memorable Trip with a Very Friendly Tour Guide and a Great Hosting.
review.reviewBody: Daniel took us to so many places in Olympic National Park i.e.  Hurricane Ridge, Elwha River, Madison Falls, Lake Crescent, and Marymere Falls. It was very memorable and set the bar high for tour guides. For breakfast, he brought some amazing pastries and orange juice. He brought magnificent food for lunch and set it down on a tablecloth with silverware and china plates and even brought wine. He went all his way to bring some cake for my birthday and made it the most special it could ever be. The trip was one of the best and I would recommend him for your tours in Seattle. His demeanor brought joy to all of us.

review.name: Best tour I've ever been on!
review.reviewBody: This was by far the best tour of our Seattle/Alaska trip!  From pickup on time, to a comfortable van ride, a more than FANTASTIC lunch, beautiful scenery in the park, waterfalls, hiking (easy) with 2 grandparents, a mom and an 11 year old.  Daniel was fantastic!  The park, the lavender farm, waterfalls, hiking.  What a day!  You can't go wrong on this great tour with Daniel.  It was our best day on our whole 2 week trip!

review.name: Perfect Day
review.reviewBody: Best day EVER! Daniel was amazing. From the time he picked us up everything was top notch. Hurricane Ridge was closed but he had other options that were amazing. We were able to visit a Lavendar Farm on the way out. He was so flexible and let us know it was our day. He would give us a time frame if we wanted to stay on schedule but if we decided we wanted to do something else ( like climb to the top of king mountain) we could but we would miss the next stop. He grew up here so knew a lot of the history and was so fun to talk to. He gave us recommendations for the next day and even told us to text him if we had questions. The views were amazing and surprising. It was well worth the money! Would definitely recommend!

review.name: Just Relax!
review.reviewBody:
A perfect day with a knowledgeable guide! My husband and I were fortunate to book the Olympic Park private day tour with Daniel. His communication even before I booked was helpful and responsive. He picked us up from our hotel in a clean and roomy luxury van, provided pastries and refreshments for the ferry ride, and offered fun and interesting information the entire day. He pointed out historical spots and made great conversation. 

The day was organized, fun, and relaxing because he took care of everything. Lunch was absolutely delicious and we could tell a lot of care had gone into its preparation. We were really impressed with Daniel's attention to detail and his knowledge of the area. We could see how much he loves the Northwest and travel in general. Highly recommend Daniel and Yonder Sky!

review.name: Wonderful Tour!
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful time thanks to our tour guide, Daniel.  He was professional, knowledgeable and a joy to spend the day with! He also provided a wonderful lunch accommodating our food allergies. All the stops were beautiful and would definitely like to return to this area. Highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Fantastic Trip
review.reviewBody:
My family and I had an absolutely wonderful time with Daniel on a tour of Olympic National Park. Since we were part of a private tour he was able to pick us up from where we were staying in Ballard rather than downtown and the Mercedes van was very spacious and comfortable. Daniel's expertise started to shine from the moment he picked us up, telling us all about Seattle and bits of area history on our drive to the ferry, before the tour really even began. As a Washington native, he really knew the history of the area including tidbits about the geology, the industries and histories of the coastal towns, the tree species, and Native peoples of the Olympic peninsula. He was also incredibly patient, allowing us plenty of time at each stop to take in the views, take pictures, rest, and helped us chose our own adventures according to our physical abilities when it came to the hiking portion of the trip at Lake Crescent. We did have some rain and fog since it was early November, but this shoulder season tour was still wonderful and really allowed us to get the true Pacific Northwest experience.

A breakfast of Macrina Bakery (local to Seattle) pastries and hot beverages was served on our morning ferry ride across the Puget Sound. Lunch was delicious and enjoyed with a view of Elwha River, despite a bit of rain at lunchtime. Daniel was also easily able to accommodate some of my mother's weird allergies without sacrificing any of the quality which we really appreciated. We had water, sodas, juices, and some delicious wine at our disposal throughout the day as well as snacks and the best shortbread for dessert.

I would highly recommend Yonder Sky tours. We will definitely look into additional tours with them in the future.

itemListElement.name: Bainbridge Island Wine and History - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch

name: Bainbridge Island Wine and History - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch
description: Experience Pacific Northwest island life, history, and wine on this all-inclusive private day tour of beautiful Bainbridge Island. We’ll start the day with a scenic ferry ride from Seattle followed by a leisurely tour of this island’s colorful past. In the afternoon, it’s all fun as we explore the island’s budding winery scene by visiting two local producers. The tour includes a gourmet lunch, admission fees, winery tasting fees, and pick-up at your Seattle hotel in our luxury Mercedes van.

review.name: A day with a Bainbridge Island local - highly recommend!
review.reviewBody: We had an excellent day in Bainbridge with local Daniel from beginning to end. From the pastries to the tour of the Japanese internment memorial to our stunning Bloedel Reserve (a must) to the gourmet lunch on the beach to the wineries to the shopping stroll to end the day, it was a perfect May day. Daniel is full of historical, local and travel information and we fully enjoyed our day with him. 5 stars!!!

itemListElement.name: Seattle Wine and Waterfall - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch

name: Seattle Wine and Waterfall - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch
description: Refine your palate at our region's renowned Woodinville wineries and experience rugged geology at Washington’s most dramatic waterfall on this private day tour to Snoqualmie Falls and Seattle wineries. Washington is now the nation’s second largest wine-producing state, and Woodinville alone has over 130 wineries. Throughout the day, you'll enjoy meaningful commentary on the history, culture, and geology of the region from an expert local guide. The tour includes a gourmet lunch at a local restaurant, wine tasting fees, and pick-up/drop-off at your Seattle hotel in our luxury Mercedes van.

itemListElement.name: Whidbey Island and Deception Pass - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch

name: Whidbey Island and Deception Pass - Private Luxury Day Tour with Lunch
description: This Whidbey Island and Deception Pass tour from Seattle highlights the best of Washington State's famous scenery and lifestyle. Washington’s largest island is packed full of local charm, friendly people, state history, and beautiful vistas. Among the most popular weekend destinations for locals, Whidbey enjoys an idyllic setting and playful energy that make it a rewarding day trip from Seattle. This private tour includes a gourmet lunch, park admissions, and pick-up/drop-off at your Seattle hotel in our luxury Mercedes van.

review.name: Time with a local well spent!
review.reviewBody: Daniel took us on a private tour of Deception Pass and Whidbey Island.  The day involved ferries and a lot of driving but the scenery was beautiful.  Daniel took us on several good hikes. We also made a stop at Fort Casey which was surprisingly interesting too. He is knowledgeable and knows the history of the area and a lot about the geology and geography in the area. He was personable and utilized the time well.

itemListElement.name: Historic Ballard: A Self-Guided Audio Tour Exploring Seattle's Quirky History

name: Historic Ballard: A Self-Guided Audio Tour Exploring Seattle's Quirky History
description:
Who says history has to be boring? Enjoy this saucy self guided audio tour of the historic Ballard neighborhood from a veteran tour guide who has heard all the great stories.

I fell in love with Ballard the first time I was introduced to it – so much so that I stayed in Seattle, learning about the city. That was over 14 years ago now! Find out for yourself why this charming city of salmon, coffee and music is so magical. 
Some of the highlights that I cover on the tour:

• A brief introduction to Seattle's early history
• Bergen Place and its Scandinavian Connection
• How Ballard was annexed by the City of Seattle
• What "Snoose Junction" was

Whether you've lived here all your life, are visiting for the first time – or anything in between – this tour is for you. You’ll find so much of the history of this quirky 19th century boomtown on Ballard Avenue. It’s an authentic slice of Seattle, with some of its most iconic buildings and establishments. Let’s take a stroll down it together.

name: Hauntingly Romantic Getaway
description:
Show your love how much you love. This hauntingly romantic getaway is your chance to stay in Port Townsend's number 1 rated hotel. This 1890 building is by far the creme of the crop when it comes to hotels in Port Townsend. The Bishop Victorian Hotel, located 1 block off main street in downtown Port Townsend, is conveniently located within easy walking distance of both uptown and downtown Port Townsend. And you get breakfast served to your room! Your package includes one night in a queen room at the hotel, dinner at the charming and amazing Alchemy Restaurant for 2, movie passes for two at the famous Rose Theater, champagne and chocolate in your room and a Twisted History tour of the amazing downtown of Port Townsend.  

One night in Port Townsend for a lifetime of memories.

Some nights may require a 2 night minimum stay. If that is the case, we will contact you and let you know.

name: Skagit Valley Tulip Festival and Deception Pass - Private Luxury Day Tour
description: Our seasonal Skagit Valley Tulip Festival and Deception Pass private tour from Seattle explores the best of spring in the Pacific Northwest. We’ll visit the temperate and fertile Skagit River Valley, home to over 450 acres of tulip fields representing 75% of U.S. commercial production. Each year, thousands of visitors from around the world travel here to witness the spectacular bloom of these magnificent flowers. After lunch, we’ll head to Deception Pass State Park, one of the most stunning landscapes in Washington. If you’re in Seattle in April, there’s no better way to spend a day.

name: Private 2-hour Walking Tour of Seattle with licensed tour guide
description:
Make the best of your visit to Seattle and explore the city most emblematic sites with a local expert. Let your guide indulge you in the secrets that the city holds. 
Alongside one of our professional tour guides, you will learn the history and stories that Seattle has to offer in this 2 hour guided walking tour. The final itinerary is of course adjustable to your personal interests about Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Seattle’s Yuletide Magic: A Christmas Wonderland Tour

name: Seattle’s Yuletide Magic: A Christmas Wonderland Tour
description:
Embark on “Seattle’s Yuletide Magic: A Christmas Wonderland Tour,” a heartwarming exploration of the city’s festive charms. Begin at Seattle Center, a wonderland of twinkling lights and holiday decorations, capturing the joyous spirit of the season. Venture to the Nitro North Building, where contemporary holiday festivities merge with traditional celebrations. The journey continues with a visit to the Space Needle, transformed into a luminous beacon of holiday cheer. Conclude your enchanting tour at Pike Place Market, a festive marketplace bustling with holiday energy, offering a treasure trove of unique gifts and delicious seasonal delights, perfectly embodying the magic of Christmas in Seattle.

*For reference only. Itineraries subject to change.

itemListElement.name: 3 Hours Couple's Massage Workshop in Fremont Court

name: 3 Hours Couple's Massage Workshop in Fremont Court
description:

We have had over 5,000 couples come through our Couple's Massage Workshops, and we have a 5-star rating pretty much everywhere. We guarantee that you will enjoy the workshop or we will give you a 100% refund.

itemListElement.name: One Hour Social Sightseeing Cruise - BYOB!

name: One Hour Social Sightseeing Cruise - BYOB!
description:
Please book as far in advance as possible as we staff based on reservations! We have 3 boats that can accommodate up to 6 guests each. You can also book this tour as a private experience from our other listing "Private One Hour Sightseeing Cruise." 
Among the best things to do in Seattle, even on a rainy day! All boats can be enclosed to keep you dry and comfortable. Explore Seattle's waterways in luxury and style with Canderé Cruising's intimate experiences for up to six guests. Offering social and private sightseeing cruises and sailing adventures, Canderé Cruising will introduce you to Seattle in ways you didn't think possible. Get up close and personal with Seattle's floating home and houseboat community, beautiful classic cruisers, modern mega yachts, and breathe taking views of Mt. Rainier, and the Seattle Skyline!

review.name: Lake Union
review.reviewBody: Great Tour of the Lake!   Very personable.  Dylan was amazing.  Couldn’t have picked a better tour. Perfect day and weather for a boat ride.

review.name: BYOB cruise!
review.reviewBody: Really nice way to see Seattle and lake Union. We had few cold ones and enjoyed a really warm day on the water. Captain had great stories!

review.name: sunny cruising
review.reviewBody: started with great directions after booked.  Captain Curt greeted us and was a wonderful host.  we wanted to see the house boats.  this was the best way.  it was very informative, relaxing and gave you a different perspective of seattle.  thanks captain curt!  he even gave us tips on our upcoming visit to alaska.

review.name: My afternoon in Seattle
review.reviewBody: I wouldn't have gotten the whole Seattle experience if it wasn't raining and it was. I enjoyed the brisk cool air on the lake. It was great ride, the skyline was amazing to see on Lake Union.  I enjoyed the history and the current about the lake. It was great to see the house Tom Hanks "lived in" from the movie Sleepless in Seattle.

review.name: Fun, relaxing, and informative
review.reviewBody: Captain Kurt was so very informative and friendly! Great little intimate boat to see Lake Union! Would highly recommend his tour verses the big boats to take a tour.

review.name: Great Time on Lake Union
review.reviewBody: Captain Kurt was a wonderful host as we toured Lake Union. He's very knowledgeable about the area and has a good sense of humor. If you're looking for a fun time in an intimate setting this is the boat tour to take.

review.name: Awesome experience
review.reviewBody: This was a awesome experience and a great way to see an learn about Seattle. The captain was awesome.!!!! He was very knowledgeable and funny. I great way also to unwind and relax, especially if you have been walking all day.

review.name: One of our highlights during our visit
review.reviewBody: We had an amazing time on the boat. It was a perfect combination of getting to know some sights and still having enough time to talk and enjoy the atmosphere with really good cocktails.

review.name: Captain Dylan is great!
review.reviewBody: Captain Dylan was an awesome guide! My girlfriend and I highly recommend! He was super nice and very knowledgeable about the city and architecture! We would definitely do that again. Canderé Cruising is the best!

review.name: Messing about in boats
review.reviewBody: Fantastic trip. Lady captain was super informative and helpful. 'Nothing like messing about in boats'. Great trip!

itemListElement.name: Mount Baker Climb Tour from Washington

name: Mount Baker Climb Tour from Washington
description: Join us for 3 days of climbing to the summit of one of North America’s most sought after peaks, Mount Baker. We take either the Easton Glacier or Coleman-Demming route with challenging route-finding through icefalls, seracs, and around large crevasses. Before summiting Mount Baker, you will learn fundamental skills necessary for safe glacier travel such as ice axe arrest, the use of crampons, and how to attach to a rope as a member of a rope team.

review.name: Great Intro to Mountaineering on a Legendary Mountain
review.reviewBody: Despite weather keeping us from getting to the summit, we walked away feeling more prepared to take it on again soon. Our guide, Josh, definitely worked hard to make our summit dreams come true, but at the same time, prioritized our safety. This meant a turn around when conditions got quite bad, and no visibility was to be had for the day. While disappointed about the weather, we were able to have extra time to learn and practice valuable skills in order to make more safe attempts in the future. Josh didn't want us to leave the mountain with only the loss of a summit and the expense of the trip, so he helped us to make sure what we learned would still be of value for future adventures. Also, just being at our snowy base camp with windows of visibility was a beautiful place to be. Great intro to mountaineering on a legendary mountain.

review.name: Two Thumbs Up
review.reviewBody: We trekked to EBC with Karma Sherpa and Parshuram Ravi as our guides. They were highly professional, flexible, courteous, knowledgeable and supportive. We requested some last minute adjustments to our travel schedule and helped fully with a smile. It was a joyful experience and I highly recommend them as well as Miyar Adventures. We also did Kilimanjaro with Miyar team. Both great experiences. Sundeep and his team are outstanding.

review.name: Amazing trip with knowledgeable guides
review.reviewBody: I had a great experience going on the Mt Baker 3 day guided climb with Miyar. Our guides Andrew and Sam were very knowledgeable and went out of their way to answer all of our questions, offer advice, and ensure that we had the best chance of summiting within our window. Miyar overall had a very professional approach towards trip planning beforehand and everything went smoothly.

review.name: Great trip and great guides!
review.reviewBody: We had a great group on our July 2021 trip. Guides were great. Knowledgeable, accommodating, and fun. Learned a lot and successfully summited which were my two goals.

review.name: Epic experience on Mt. Baker
review.reviewBody: Myself and my daughter (age 10) climbed Mt. Baker with Miyar Adventures via Easton Glacier route, Simon was our guide. This was part of a 4 day Glacier travel course. The whole experience was epic in many ways. Simon's knowledge is excellent, I would trust him 100% in any situations that may come up on the mountain. We learned a lot and is was fun. The overall organization from Miyar was great (including informational emails from Jake and communication with Sandeep). Great company that I would choose again in a heartbeat.

review.name: Great summit experience
review.reviewBody: We had a great time summiting Mt Baker via Coleman-Deming route with Miyar Adventures. Big shout out to our guides Drew and Sam, who teach us essential mountaineering skills and lead us to summit and downhill safely and fun. Looking forward to getting back to the mountains soon with Miyar!

review.name: Great summit experience!
review.reviewBody: It was a memorable experience climbing Mt Baker with Miyar Adventures. Simon was our guide and he comes with excellent climbing experience. We felt very comfortable and safe in his rope team on sections like Colfax peak and Roman wall.  We got a chance to interact with Sam and Bailey as the other guides and they were equally great and helpful. Climbing with Sandeep is always fun. I look forward to many more climbs with Miyar.

review.name: Excellent climb
review.reviewBody:
We climbed Mt Baker with Miyar Adventure. The guides were Simon and Sam, both were great.  They came with excellent mountain climbing experience and knowledge, and helped making all of us comfortable in this hard climb.    They both worked hard to address our concerns,  anticipated and handled difficult situations throughout the whole trip.  Safety was always put at the first priority.     

I look forward to another adventure  with Miyar !

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: It was a great experience summiting Baker with Miyar Adventures. A big shout out to all the guides ( Caleb , Sam, Jalen and Ryan ) specially Caleb who was our guide. He made me feel very comfortable in the climb and it will be one of the great memorable climb. Thanks to Sandeep and Jake for patiently responding to all our questions . Looking forward to do more climbs with Miyar adventures..

review.name: An unforgettable Baker Experience!
review.reviewBody: My friend and I did the 3 day North Ridge ascent on Mount Baker with Caleb as our guide. It was truly a life-giving, unforgettable experience. We were unable to summit due to a change in weather conditions at the top, but Caleb made the call to prioritize our safety and I cannot thank him enough for that. Through challenges and unexpected events, we felt supported and safe with such a knowledgeable, experienced and thoughtful guide. Sandeep, the owner of Miyar, worked with us from the very beginning to get us an experience we were hoping for. Our expectations were blown out of the water! I would recommend everyone plans their climbing adventure with Miyar's team, they are second to none. Thank you!!!

itemListElement.name: Self-Guided Seattle Scavenger Hunt: Plunging Seattle’s Depths

name: Self-Guided Seattle Scavenger Hunt: Plunging Seattle’s Depths
description:
Downtown Seattle is where it all began, transforming from a small logging town into one of America’s greatest cities. On today’s epic adventure hunt, we’ll loop through Pioneer Square, Downtown, and Chinatown, seeking out public art, monumental buildings, and diverse cultures—from Sunday morning mahjong to Monday Night Football. Strap on those walking shoes, gather your friends, and book your adventure around Downtown Seattle today!

What You'll See: Pioneer Square, Chinatown, CenturyLink Field

review.name: Scavenger hunt!
review.reviewBody: So much fun I highly recommend doing this but be aware you must walk up ver steep hills! We did it with strollers and it was difficult

name: Mount Rainier Tour from Seattle
description:
Private tour for 2-5 guests.

SUMMER: Visit Mount Rainier National Park on this full-day tour. See waterfalls, old-growth forests, flowering meadows, and wildlife in their natural habitat. This experience on Mount Rainier makes your expected stops — but also ventures off the beaten path, with fantastic views and vistas, waterfalls, and park grounds. This tour travels all the way around Mount Rainier, and the different landscapes are fantastic. Four stops for trail walks and/or waterfalls are included.  
FALL AND WINTER: MAY HAVE SNOW!

review.name: We saw all the best spots that included all the waterfalls and the best views of Mount Rainier.
review.reviewBody: Beautiful trip.  Cheryl is an educated, personable guide that makes you feel welcome right from the start.  It felt like she was a friend on the trip with us.

review.name: Mt Rainier
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was great!  She knows the park like the back of her hand, and even found us the perfect picnic spot with a fantastic view of Mt Rainier.  She made the ride to the park and back a blast!  Thanks Cheryl!

review.name: Worth Every Penny
review.reviewBody: The trip was delightful.  It became overcast and rainy, so the weather did not cooperate, but within the limitations of that Cheryl took us to see the most breathtaking sights.  We experienced everything from sunshine to rain to snow, and experienced awesome scenery.  Picking up on our frequent trips to the Smoky Mountains, she made sure we were able to witness plenty of what made the Mount Rainer area unique.  We saw enormous pine trees, beautiful waterfalls, and the mountains clothed in snow.  She was informative, and knew the mountains extremely well.  She was great company and an excellent guide.  And she took us to a wonderful restaurant in a converted railroad passenger car that was a unique treat.  We returned to Seattle on secondary roads and saw a good deal of what Washington State was like around the Cascades.   I'm glad we took her tour.

review.name: Mount Rainier Tour July 19, 2023
review.reviewBody: We initially booked a tour of Mt. St. Helens as a pre-cruise trip. Unfortunately the road to the visitor's center was washed out in a mudslide so Cheryl suggested switching to Mt. Rainier. It ended up being a fantastic day. The mountain and surrounding national park are spectacular to visit. Cheryl knew all the good spots for pictures, hikes, a scenic lunch and park history. She also knew a lot about what we saw and explained it well. We would recommend her tours to anyone.

review.name: Best way to see Mt Ranier!
review.reviewBody: This was the most wonderful way to see Mt Ranier! Cheryl was our guide and since it was a private tour we were able to see the day as we pleased. We could stay longer at some stops and move faster through others and no feeling of being part of a crowded group so better picture taking opportunities.  She also gave us great history of the area on the drives and was very knowledgeable about the flora, fauna, and history of the Mt. Ranier area. I was originally booked on a small guided tour of 10 people but so glad I changed my mind and paid just a little extra to go private with Cheryl. She offers other tours of the area as well, would definitely book with her again and recommend to anyone!

review.name: Beautiful Views
review.reviewBody:
Besides the beautiful weather,  
and Mount Rainer scenery, we got to see a large rainbow at the bottom of the waterfall.  Private tour was so worth it; even catered to my food allergies.  Thanks Janet and Cheryl!

review.name: Private Mt. Rainier Tour!
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful tour of the bottom third of the mountain with views of the entire peak! The best thing about the private tour is that regardless of your conditioning, your level of adventure, or your particular interest, this tour allows the flexibility to see and experience what you want (within reason, of course!) The guide was knowledgeable and they allow you to take the basic tour and customize it. I really appreciated the flexibility with my 13 year old sons enthusiasm and provided a one of a kind unique  experience for us! I highly recommend for anyone wanting to visit Rainier and not be shoved into a cattle bus. It's totally worth the price difference (if any), especially since we were coming all the way across the country from Florida. A truly unforgettable once in a lifetime experience. Thank you Cheryl's Tours!

name: Private Pacific Ocean Beach Experience
description: Seeing the Pacific Ocean beach is wonderful at Long Beach. You will see the powder gray sand that goes on for miles. Visit a lighthouse high above the beach, eat some great food, and see what used to be the worlds largest frying pan! Plenty of time to enjoy the beaches and trails.

name: WildLights at Woodland Park Zoo
description: Come see wild animals and wild places recreated in hundreds of thousands of sparkling LED lights at WildLights presented by Sound Credit Union! Enjoy up close animal encounters, visit our giant Lite Brite (NEW!), have a faux-snowball fight with your family, enjoy carolers and get warm and toasty at one of many fire pits located across the zoo.

review.name: Night time, wild lights
review.reviewBody:
It was our first time going to the wildlights. Many have recommended. And it was really beautiful. I was with my parents, we are from Brazil. So the cold wasn't easy to deal with. Windy. And freezing cold for us. However, the lights were amazing. Scenes created, animals all around. The flowers, butterflies. Everything was just amazing. If we weren't to cold, we would have stayed longer.
But it is really worth going!!

review.name: Perfect way to celebrate the season!
review.reviewBody: Last night was the last chance to enjoy the lights at the Woodland Park Wildlights for this year.  After enjoying an awesome dinner at Uneeda Burger, we strolled up to the park for a first time visit to the zoo lights. If you are driving, Parking is free for the evening event. It was a beautiful night with no rain. Every time we were a little chilled, we stopped by one of the fire pits to warm up.  The lights were beautiful and they had a bunch of beautiful animal themed characters.  There were also several special kid friendly activities like a snowless snowball room.  We plan to do this again next winter.

name: Seattle Private Tour for 2-5
description:
Private tour for just your party. No additional guests.

See Seattle, in style and on your own, with your personal driver and guide.

We'll start you out with our usual wish list from customers, and personalize it for what you like! 

Space Needle, Chihuly Garden and Glass, Ballard Locks and Fish Ladder, Alki's sandy beaches, historic Pioneer Square, Amazon Headquarters.

review.name: We got to know Seattle
review.reviewBody: What a terrific day we had with Cheryl. From the complementary water bottles to the comfortable SUV and Cheryl’s warm personality,  we were off to a great start. Our tour took us to the many neighborhoods of Seattle. Cheryl explained the history of the city. We enjoyed the fishing docks and the fish ladder and a car tour of Pike Place. All in all, it was a wonderful experience. Thanks, Cheryl.
